.TH "i40iw_find_pd_index_limit" 9 "i40iw_find_pd_index_limit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40iw_find_pd_index_limit \- finds page descriptor index limit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" i40iw_find_pd_index_limit
.BI "(struct i40iw_hmc_info *hmc_info "  ","
.BI "u32 type "  ","
.BI "u32 idx "  ","
.BI "u32 cnt "  ","
.BI "u32 *pd_idx "  ","
.BI "u32 *pd_limit "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hmc_info" 12
pointer to the HMC configuration information struct
.IP "type" 12
HMC resource type we're examining
.IP "idx" 12
starting index for the object
.IP "cnt" 12
number of objects we're trying to create
.IP "pd_idx" 12
pointer to return page descriptor index
.IP "pd_limit" 12
pointer to return page descriptor index limit
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calculates the page descriptor index and index limit for the resource
defined by i40iw_hmc_rsrc_type.
